## Why This Is Asked

Tests practical design of online ICA under non-stationarity and real-time constraints, a common challenge in wearables and streaming data.

## Key Concepts

- Online ICA with streaming whitening
- Adaptive contrast/Nonlinearity choices
- Drift tracking for sign and permutation

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo online ICA update (simplified)
function updateUnmixing(W, X_batch) {
  const Y = W.map(row => dot(row, X_batch));
  // compute a simple contrast derivative estimate
  const dW = computeGradient(Y, X_batch);
  // stochastic update
  return W.map((w, i) => normalizeVector(subtract(w, scale(dW[i], 0.01))));
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you quantify independence in streaming data?
- How would you adapt this approach to changing channel counts or missing data?
